{"title_page": "Bordj Mena\u00efel", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Bordj Mena\u00efel\n|native_name            = {{lang|ar|\u0628\u0631\u062c \u0645\u0646\u0627\u064a\u0644}}\n|nickname               = Bur\u01e7 Imnayen\n|settlement_type        = City and Common\n|motto                  = \"From the people, for the people\"\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              = DZ 35 Bordj Menaiel.svg\n|mapsize                = 180px\n|map_caption            = Location of Bordj Mena\u00efel in the [[Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n|pushpin_map            = Algeria\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Bordj Mena\u00efel in the [[Algeria]]\n|coordinates              = {{coord|36.741667|3.723056|type:city_region:DZ|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           =\n|subdivision_type         = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{flag|Algeria}}\n|subdivision_type1        = [[Provinces of Algeria|Province]] \n|subdivision_name1        = [[Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[Districts of Algeria|District]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Bordj Mena\u00efel District]]\n|subdivision_type3        = \n|subdivision_name3        = \n|government_footnotes     =\n|government_type          = [[Municipality]]\n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = \n|established_title        = APC\n|established_date         = 2012-2017\n|area_magnitude           = \n|unit_pref                = Imperial \n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_land_km2            = \n|population_as_of         = 2008\n|population_footnotes     =\n|population_note          =\n|population_total         = 64820<ref>[http://www.ons.dz/collections/w35_p2.pdf ONS Statistic (Boumerd\u00e8s province)] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6F570aXoE?url=http://www.ons.dz/collections/w35_p2.pdf |date=2013-03-13 }}</ref>\n|population_density_km2   = \n|timezone                 = [[Central European Time|CET]] \n|utc_offset               =  +1\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = \n|elevation_ft             = \n|iso_code                 = CP\n|postal_code_type         = [[List of postal codes in Algeria|Postal code]]\n|postal_code              = \n|area_code                =\n|blank_name               =\n|blank_info               =\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n}}\n\n'''Bordj Mena\u00efel''' (from the [[Arabic]] \u0628\u0631\u062c - bordj, \"tower\" and [[Berber languages|Berber]] ''imnayen'' \"cavaliers\") is a town in the [[Boumerd\u00e8s Province]] in [[Algeria]].  It is located in the western [[Kabylie]] region at {{Coord|36|44|30|N|3|43|23|E}} and is 30&nbsp;km away from the city of [[Boumerd\u00e8s]]. As of 2008, the population of the municipality is 64,820.<ref>[https://www.wilaya-boumerdes.dz/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=72&Itemid=114]</ref>\n\n==History==\nBordj Mena\u00efel was founded by the [[Ottoman Algeria|Ottoman government of Algeria]], probably in the 16th century, to guard a route between [[Algiers]] and [[Constantine, Algeria|Constantine]] and to secure control of the [[Isser District|Isser]] plain<ref>N. Robin, 1873, \"[https://books.google.fr/books?id=jM0OAAAAQAAJ&dq=mena%C3%AFel%20turcs&pg=PA132#v=onepage&q=mena%C3%AFel%20turcs&f=false Note sur l'organisation militaire et administrative des Turcs dans la Grande Kabylie]\", ''Revue Africaine'', p. 134.</ref>.  In the 18th century its military role was superseded by the foundation of [[Bordj Sebaou]] further west, but it remained the residence of the Ottoman oukil administering the surrounding farmland<ref>N. Robin, 1873, \"[https://books.google.fr/books?id=jM0OAAAAQAAJ&dq=mena%C3%AFel%20turcs&pg=PA207#v=onepage&q=menaiel&f=false Note sur l'organisation militaire et administrative des Turcs dans la Grande Kabylie]\", ''Revue Africaine'', p. 207.</ref>.\n\nThe [[French Algeria|French conquest]] reached the fort of Bordj Mena\u00efel in 1844, when General [[Thomas Robert Bugeaud|Bugeaud]] took it.  Afterwards, it initially became the residence of the aghas of the [[Iflissen Umellil]]<ref>Robin 1873:207.</ref>.  In 1859, a French colony was created there by imperial decree, using 1718 hectares.  It was enlarged through land expropriation in 1872 by Admiral [[Louis Henri de Gueydon|de Gueydon]], in the wake of the [[Mokrani Revolt]]<ref>Charles-Claude Bernard, 1877, ''[http://biblio.univ-alger.dz/jspui/bitstream/1635/27/1/22400.pdf Notice topographique et m\u00e9dicale sur le plaine d'Isser]'', pp. 36-39</ref>.\n\n==Transport==\nThe road RN 12 runs through Bordj Mena\u00efel, linking it with [[Issers|Isser]] to the west and [[Naciria]] to the east.<ref>[http://www.mtp.gov.dz/fr/permalink/3276.html Atlas Routier de l'Alg\u00e9rie : Wilaya de Boumerd\u00e8s]</ref>\n\n==Sports==\nAlgeria goalkeeper [[Faouzi Chaouchi]] was born in Bordj Menaiel.  The local football team is [[JS Bordj M\u00e9na\u00efel]].\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Farouk Belka\u00efd]], footballer\n* [[Bachir Boudjelid]], footballer\n* [[Faouzi Chaouchi]], footballer\n* [[Zinedine Ferhat]], footballer\n* [[Marthe Simard]], Canadian politician\n* [[Fatma Zohra Zamoum]], writer and film-maker\n\n==References==\n* Charles-Claude Bernard, 1877. ''Notice topographique et m\u00e9dicale sur le plaine d'Isser''. Blida: A. Mauguin.\n* Kouider Djouab, 2017. ''[https://www.edilivre.com/mag/frontwidget/preview/book/id/861881/ Bordj-Mena\u00efel, une ville, une histoire : La Ville des coquelicots]''. Saint Denis: Edilivre.\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bordj Menaiel}}\n{{Boumerd\u00e8s-geo-stub}}\n{{Boumerd\u00e8s Province}}\n\n[[Category: Populated places in Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n[[Category: Communes of Algeria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Bordj Mena\u00efel\n|native_name            = {{lang|ar|\u0628\u0631\u062c \u0645\u0646\u0627\u064a\u0644}}\n|nickname               = Bur\u01e7 Imnayen\n|settlement_type        = City and Common\n|motto                  = \"From the people, for the people\"\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              = DZ 35 Bordj Menaiel.svg\n|mapsize                = 180px\n|map_caption            = Location of Bordj Mena\u00efel in the [[Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n|pushpin_map            = Algeria\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Bordj Mena\u00efel in the [[Algeria]]\n|coordinates              = {{coord|36.741667|3.723056|type:city_region:DZ|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           =\n|subdivision_type         = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{flag|Algeria}}\n|subdivision_type1        = [[Provinces of Algeria|Province]] \n|subdivision_name1        = [[Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[Districts of Algeria|District]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Bordj Mena\u00efel District]]\n|subdivision_type3        = \n|subdivision_name3        = \n|government_footnotes     =\n|government_type          = [[Municipality]]\n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = \n|established_title        = APC\n|established_date         = 2012-2017\n|area_magnitude           = \n|unit_pref                = Imperial \n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_land_km2            = \n|population_as_of         = 2008\n|population_footnotes     =\n|population_note          =\n|population_total         = 64820<ref>[http://www.ons.dz/collections/w35_p2.pdf ONS Statistic