g=PA207#v=onepage&q=menaiel&f=false Note sur l'organisation militaire et administrative des Turcs dans la Grande Kabylie]\", ''Revue Africaine'', p. 207.</ref>.\n\nThe [[French Algeria|French conquest]] reached the fort of Bordj Mena\u00efel in 1844, when General [[Thomas Robert Bugeaud|Bugeaud]] took it.  Afterwards, it initially became the residence of the aghas of the [[Iflissen Umellil]]<ref>Robin 1873:207.</ref>.  In 1859, a French colony was created there by imperial decree, using 1718 hectares.  It was enlarged through land expropriation in 1872 by Admiral [[Louis Henri de Gueydon|de Gueydon]], in the wake of the [[Mokrani Revolt]]<ref>Charles-Claude Bernard, 1877, ''[http://biblio.univ-alger.dz/jspui/bitstream/1635/27/1/22400.pdf Notice topographique et m\u00e9dicale sur le plaine d'Isser]'', pp. 36-39</ref>.\n\n==Transport==\nThe road RN 12 runs through Bordj Mena\u00efel, linking it with [[Issers|Isser]] to the west and [[Naciria]] to the east.<ref>[http://www.mtp.gov.dz/fr/permalink/3276.html Atlas Routier de l'Alg\u00e9rie : Wilaya de Boumerd\u00e8s]</ref>\n\n==Sports==\nAlgeria goalkeeper [[Faouzi Chaouchi]] was born in Bordj Menaiel.  The local football team is [[JS Bordj M\u00e9na\u00efel]].\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Farouk Belka\u00efd]], footballer\n* [[Bachir Boudjelid]], footballer\n* [[Faouzi Chaouchi]], footballer\n* [[Zinedine Ferhat]], footballer\n* [[Marthe Simard]], Canadian politician\n* [[Fatma Zohra Zamoum]], writer and film-maker\n\n==References==\n* Charles-Claude Bernard, 1877. ''Notice topographique et m\u00e9dicale sur le plaine d'Isser''. Blida: A. Mauguin.\n* Kouider Djouab, 2017. ''[https://www.edilivre.com/mag/frontwidget/preview/book/id/861881/ Bordj-Mena\u00efel, une ville, une histoire : La Ville des coquelicots]''. Saint Denis: Edilivre.\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bordj Menaiel}}\n{{Boumerd\u00e8s-geo-stub}}\n{{Boumerd\u00e8s Province}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Boumerd\u00e8s Province]]\n[[Category:C